		<item>
		<title>Calls Grow for U.K. Prime Minister Starmer to Resign as Mandelson, Epstein Row Implodes</title>
		<link>https://time.com/7373067/united-kingdom-keir-starmer-demands-for-resignation-epstein-mandelson/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Callum Sutherland]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 09 Feb 2026 18:34:19 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[News Desk]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://time.com/?p=7373067</guid>

					<description><![CDATA["For the good of the party and for the good of the country, we're going to need a change," said one Labour lawmaker.]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<aside class="right-rail__container right-rail__container--ad"><div class="right-rail__ad__wrapper right-rail__module"><div class="right-rail__ad" id="right-rail__ad-7373067"></div></div>
<div class="OUTBRAIN right-rail__outbrain right-rail__module" data-src="https://time.com/7373067/united-kingdom-keir-starmer-demands-for-resignation-epstein-mandelson/" data-widget-id="SB_2" data-ob-template="timemag"></div></aside>

<img decoding="async" class="wp-block-gutenberg-custom-blocks-featured-media" src="https://api.time.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Screenshot-2026-02-09-at-18.10.24.png" alt=""/>



<p>British Prime Minister Keir Starmer is facing growing calls to resign <a href="https://time.com/7372763/epstein-files-united-kingdom-peter-mandelson-prince-andrew-starmer/" >amid the fallout</a> from his former Labour colleague Peter Mandelson&rsquo;s relationship with convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein.</p>



<p>Anas Sarwar, leader of the Scottish Labour Party, <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Reuters/videos/802890309491041/"  target="_blank">urged</a> Starmer to step down during a press conference on Monday afternoon.</p>

[time-brightcove not-tgx=&#8221;true&#8221;]



<p>&ldquo;This isn&#8217;t easy, and it&#8217;s not without pain, as I have a genuine friendship with Keir Starmer, but my first priority and my first loyalty is to my country, Scotland,&rdquo; he said, citing fears that the scandal in Westminster risks overshadowing the Scottish Parliament election in May. &ldquo;The distraction needs to end, and the leadership in Downing Street has to change.&rdquo;</p>



<p>Sarwar faced questions himself this past week when a <a href="https://x.com/AnasSarwar/status/1908204710143942907?ref=ed_direct"  target="_blank">resurfaced social media post</a> showed him referring to Mandelson as an &ldquo;old friend&rdquo; after they shared a meeting last April. The Scottish lawmaker defended the meeting once more on Monday, saying Mandelson shouldn&rsquo;t have been in office in the first place.</p>



<p>Starmer&rsquo;s chief of staff Morgan McSweeney resigned from his position over the weekend, claiming responsibility for advising Starmer to appoint Mandelson as the U.K. ambassador to Washington&mdash;a move that is under increasing scrutiny, as the lawmaker&#8217;s ties to Epstein were known to some extent.</p>



<p>Tim Allan, Starmer&rsquo;s director of communications, followed suit on Monday, resigning from his position in what appeared to be an attempt to ease the pressure on Starmer.</p>



<p>But for some, it&rsquo;s not enough.</p>



<p><strong>Read More</strong>: <em><a href="https://time.com/7372763/epstein-files-united-kingdom-peter-mandelson-prince-andrew-starmer/" >How the Epstein Files Broke Britain</a></em></p>



<p>Mandelson was <a href="https://time.com/7316349/peter-mandelson-fired-uk-ambassador-united-states-epstein-controversy/" >sacked</a> from the role of ambassador in September after a previous release of files showed that his relationship with Epstein stretched beyond what was previously known. </p>



<p>That appointment is under renewed <a href="https://time.com/7372763/epstein-files-united-kingdom-peter-mandelson-prince-andrew-starmer/" >inspection</a> as emails from the latest release of files appear to show Mandelson <a href="https://www.justice.gov/epstein/files/DataSet%209/EFTA00775718.pdf"  target="_blank">leaked</a> sensitive government information to Epstein during his time as Business Secretary under then-Prime Minister Gordon Brown. A <a href="https://news.met.police.uk/news/update-searches-concluded-re-misconduct-in-public-office-investigation-505947"  target="_blank">police investigation</a> into Mandelson for alleged misconduct in public office offences is now underway.</p>



<p>Mandelson resigned from the Labour Party and stepped down from the House of Lords last week. Amid calls for Starmer to follow suit, a spokesperson for the Prime Minister on Monday said he will not be resigning.</p>



<p> &ldquo;The Prime Minister is concentrating on the job in hand. He is getting on with the job of delivering change across the country,&rdquo; the spokesperson said, adding that Starmer is &ldquo;confident&rdquo; he has the full support of his Cabinet. Many Cabinet members have since rallied around the Prime Minister, with Home Secretary Shabana Mahmood and Deputy Prime Minister David Lammy among those vocalizing their support.</p>



<p>However, Starmer&rsquo;s premiership remains under scrutiny and some lawmakers are urging him to consider stepping down.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Brian Leishman</strong></h2>



<p>Brian Leishman, a Scottish member of the Labour Party, fully supported Sarwar&rsquo;s message on Monday.</p>



<p>&ldquo;I have said that Keir Starmer&rsquo;s position is untenable and that it is in the country&rsquo;s best interest for him to step down and for the government to have a change in direction,&rdquo; Leishman said in a statement to TIME.&nbsp;</p>



<p>&ldquo;Sarwar has shown that he and Scottish Labour will act in the best interests of our country,&rdquo; Leishman added, urging a return to &rdquo;real Labour values.&rdquo;</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Ian Byrne</strong></h2>



<p>Ian Byrne is among the Labour lawmakers who welcomed McSweeney&rsquo;s resignation on Sunday, describing it as being in &ldquo;the best interests of the government.&rdquo;</p>



<p>He <a href="https://x.com/IanByrneMP/status/2020554763868205420"  target="_blank">claimed</a> Starmer&rsquo;s chief of staff had &ldquo;overseen the erosion of internal democracy and the normalization of a deeply damaging factionalism that members and MPs are now living with.&rdquo;</p>



<p>But McSweeney&rsquo;s resignation is not enough, according to Byrne.&nbsp;</p>



<p>&ldquo;A true change in political direction must now come from&mdash;and be led from&mdash;the very top,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;The PM must now reflect honestly on his own position and ask whether, for the good of the country and the Labour Party, he should follow McSweeney&rsquo;s lead.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Neil Duncan-Jordan</strong></h2>



<p>Neil Duncan-Jordan of the Labour Party said: &ldquo;We can&#8217;t just keep going on like this, lurching from one crisis to the next, and one of the best ways of resetting is to have renewal, and that means changing who&#8217;s in charge.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>



<p>When asked during an interview with <a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/sounds/play/m002qhtd"  target="_blank">BBC Radio Solent</a> who should replace Starmer as Prime Minister, Duncan-Jordan pointed to the Mayor of Greater Manchester, Andy Burnham. </p>



<p>Labour&rsquo;s National Executive Committee (NEC) recently blocked Burnham from standing in the Gorton and Denton by-election, prompting much tension.</p>



<p>&ldquo;We need to recognize that, for the good of the party and for the good of the country, we&#8217;re going to need a change,&rdquo; said Duncan-Jordan, citing other grievances he had with decisions made by Starmer during his premiership so far, such as a suggestion for means-tested winter fuel allowance and proposed amendments to <a href="https://time.com/7299472/united-kingdom-welfare-bill-controversy-starmer-rebellion/" >disability benefits</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Kemi Badenoch</strong></h2>



<p>Leader of the opposition Conservative Party, Kemi Badenoch, has strongly pushed for Starmer to resign since putting pressure on the Prime Minister in the House of Commons last week to answer questions over his appointment of Mandelson.</p>



<p>&ldquo;His [Starmer] position now is untenable, because if he thinks that bad advice is enough for Morgan McSweeney to go, then yes, I think that makes his position untenable,&rdquo; Badenoch said in an <a href="https://x.com/BBCr4today/status/2020786031100928165"  target="_blank">interview</a> with the BBC on Monday.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Badenoch went on to criticize Starmer&rsquo;s handling of the entire Mandelson situation.</p>



<p>&ldquo;He needs to start governing the country. Everybody makes mistakes. How you handle them shows what sort of character you are. And what he is showing is that he is weak,&rdquo; she claimed.</p>



<p>Refusing to suggest an ideal replacement, should Starmer step down, Badenoch said: &ldquo;I don&#8217;t think there is a single better person on the Labour benches. Let&#8217;s just be clear&mdash;the problem is the Labour Party.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
		<post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1">7373067</post-id>	</item>
		<item>
		<title>Buckingham Palace &#8216;Ready to Support&#8217; Police If Contacted Over Andrew Allegations Amid Epstein Row</title>
		<link>https://time.com/7373053/prince-william-kate-middleton-address-epstein-files-andrew-scandal/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Olivia-Anne Cleary]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 09 Feb 2026 12:28:19 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[News Desk]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://time.com/?p=7373053</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor (formerly known as Prince Andrew), is mentioned throughout the Epstein files.]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<aside class="right-rail__container right-rail__container--ad"><div class="right-rail__ad__wrapper right-rail__module"><div class="right-rail__ad" id="right-rail__ad-7373053"></div></div>
<div class="OUTBRAIN right-rail__outbrain right-rail__module" data-src="https://time.com/7373053/prince-william-kate-middleton-address-epstein-files-andrew-scandal/" data-widget-id="SB_2" data-ob-template="timemag"></div></aside>

<img decoding="async" class="wp-block-gutenberg-custom-blocks-featured-media" src="https://api.time.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/GettyImages-2235224480.jpg" alt="TOPSHOT-BRITAIN-ROYALS-DEATH"/>



<p>Buckingham Palace said King Charles III will, if approached, support police as they assess claims related to his brother, Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor, and his ties to the late convicted sex offender <a href="https://time.com/7372763/epstein-files-united-kingdom-peter-mandelson-prince-andrew-starmer/" >Jeffrey Epstein</a>.</p>



<p>&ldquo;The King has made clear, in words and through unprecedented actions, his profound concern at allegations which continue to come to light in respect of Mr. Mountbatten-Windsor&rsquo;s conduct,&rdquo; the statement read. &ldquo;While the specific claims in question are for Mr. Mountbatten-Windsor to address, if we are approached by Thames Valley Police, we stand ready to support them as you would expect.&rdquo;</p>
[time-brightcove not-tgx=&#8221;true&#8221;]




<p>The statement came hours after Thames Valley Police confirmed to TIME that they are &ldquo;assessing the information&rdquo; regarding allegations that Andrew&mdash;while serving as the U.K. trade envoy&mdash;shared confidential government reports with Epstein, detailing trips to Singapore, China, Hong Kong, and Vietnam in 2010 and 2011.</p>



<p>Last week, the same police force confirmed they are reviewing a fresh allegation that Epstein sent a woman to Andrew at the Royal Lodge residence in Windsor in 2010.</p>



<p>&ldquo;We are aware of reports about a woman said to have been taken to an address in Windsor in 2010 for sexual purposes,&rdquo; a police spokesperson told TIME. &ldquo;We are assessing the information in line with our established procedures.&rdquo;</p>



<p>TIME has reached out to Andrew&rsquo;s representatives for comment.</p>



<p>Andrew (formerly known as Prince Andrew) is under renewed scrutiny following the U.S. Department of Justice&#8217;s latest <a href="https://time.com/7372763/epstein-files-united-kingdom-peter-mandelson-prince-andrew-starmer/" >release of files</a> connected to Epstein. The <a href="https://time.com/7362936/epstein-files-india-slovakia/" >documents</a> include a photograph of Andrew leaning over a woman on the floor. The woman&rsquo;s face has been redacted and it&rsquo;s unclear when or where the photograph was taken.</p>



<p>Prince William and Kate Middleton addressed the files on Monday morning.</p>



<p>&ldquo;I can confirm the Prince and Princess have been deeply concerned by the continuing revelations. Their thoughts remain focused on the victims,&rdquo; said a Kensington Palace spokesperson on behalf of the couple.</p>



<p>And they&#8217;re not the only royals to speak up, as Andrew&rsquo;s younger brother Prince Edward, when asked about the release of the new files during a summit in Dubai last week, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KK5ZAc3JY68&amp;t=16s"  target="_blank">said</a>: &ldquo;It&rsquo;s really important, always, to remember the victims, and who are the victims in all of this? [There are] a lot of victims in this.&rdquo;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-gutenberg-custom-blocks-inline-image"><img decoding="async" src="https://api.time.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Screenshot-2026-02-09-at-12.01.53.png" alt="" alignment="original-size-image"/><p class="article_header"></p><p class="article_subheading"></p><p class="article_text"></p></figure>



<p>Epstein was initially sentenced to 18 months imprisonment in 2008 after pleading guilty to state charges&mdash;one count of soliciting prostitution and one count of soliciting prostitution from someone under the age of 18. He was in custody once more awaiting trial on federal charges for the sex trafficking of minors when he <a href="https://time.com/5649271/jeffrey-epstein-suicide/" >died in a New York jail cell</a> in 2019.</p>



<p>Andrew&rsquo;s relationship with Epstein&mdash;and the fact he continued communicating with the disgraced financier after his initial conviction&mdash;has long been scrutinized.</p>



<p>The royal was famously interviewed on BBC&rsquo;s <a href="https://time.com/6963952/scoop-netflix-true-story/" ><em>Newsnight</em></a> in 2019 and questioned over why he visited Epstein in New York in 2010. (The pair were pictured walking through Central Park together during the trip.)</p>



<p>Andrew was accused of sexual abuse himself by one of Epstein&rsquo;s most prominent victims, the late Virginia Giuffre. He strongly denied the allegations.</p>



<p>In January 2022, Andrew was stripped of his key military titles and royal patronages in the midst of a civil sexual abuse case brought forward by Giuffre. A month later, <a href="https://time.com/7326183/epstein-victim-virginia-giuffre-ghislaine-maxwell-memoir/" >he settled the lawsuit</a> with Giuffre for an undisclosed amount.</p>



<p>Andrew was stripped of the remainder of his titles in late 2025, after additional allegations by <a href="https://time.com/7333355/virginia-giuffre-jeffrey-epstein-donald-trump-emails/" >Giuffre (who died in April 2025)</a> came to light in her <a href="https://time.com/7326183/epstein-victim-virginia-giuffre-ghislaine-maxwell-memoir/" >posthumous memoir</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-gutenberg-custom-blocks-inline-image"><img decoding="async" src="https://api.time.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/GettyImages-2211141145.jpg" alt="King Charles III And Queen Camilla Attend The 2025 Easter Service At St George's Chapel" alignment="original-size-image"/><p class="article_header"></p><p class="article_subheading"></p><p class="article_text"></p></figure>



<p>Sarah Ferguson, Andrew&rsquo;s ex-wife and the mother of his two daughters, has also faced renewed questioning over her own relationship with Epstein following mentions in the latest release of Epstein files. (The emails do not indicate any wrongdoing, nor is appearing in the files an indication of wrongdoing.)</p>



<p>According to the emails, Ferguson <a href="https://www.justice.gov/epstein/files/DataSet%2010/EFTA01857789.pdf"  target="_blank">continued communicating</a> with Epstein after his initial conviction.</p>



<p>In September, <a href="https://time.com/7319567/duchess-of-york-sarah-ferguson-jeffrey-epstein-email-controversy/" >multiple charities cut ties with Ferguson</a> after a previous drop of files revealed she had emailed Epstein and referred to him as a &ldquo;supreme friend.&rdquo; A spokesperson for Ferguson pointed to the former duchess&rsquo; &ldquo;<a href="https://news.sky.com/story/duchess-of-york-says-gushing-message-to-epstein-was-not-what-it-seemed-13435313"  target="_blank">regret</a>&rdquo; over her association with the financier.</p>



<hr/>



<p>While the revelations from the Epstein files continue to rock the royal family, the British government is also engulfed in controversy following the latest release of documents.</p>



<p>U.K. Prime Minister Keir Starmer is in crisis, facing serious questions over his decision to appoint Peter Mandelson as the U.K. ambassador to the U.S. in early 2025, despite it being known that he had a history with Epstein.</p>



<p><a href="https://time.com/7316349/peter-mandelson-fired-uk-ambassador-united-states-epstein-controversy/" >Mandelson was sacked as ambassador</a> in September after it came to light that he shared a closer relationship with Epstein than he&rsquo;d previously disclosed. The emails released by the DOJ in January proved to be even more damning, as they appear to show that Mandelson&mdash;while serving as Business Secretary under then-Prime Minister Gordon Brown&mdash;may have leaked sensitive <a href="https://www.justice.gov/epstein/files/DataSet%209/EFTA00775718.pdf"  target="_blank">government information</a> to Epstein in 2009.</p>



<p>Mandelson resigned from the ruling Labour Party last week, saying that he wanted to avoid causing it &ldquo;further embarrassment.&rdquo; He also stepped down from the House of Lords.</p>



<p>The U.K.&rsquo;s Metropolitan Police has <a href="https://news.met.police.uk/news/investigation-launched-into-alleged-misconduct-in-public-office-505806"  target="_blank">launched</a> an investigation into Mandelson &ldquo;for misconduct in public office offences.&rdquo; On Friday afternoon, local time, police <a href="https://news.met.police.uk/news/update-on-investigation-into-misconduct-in-public-office-offences-505940"  target="_blank">revealed</a> two properties linked to the former government minister had been searched in relation to the probe. Mandelson has not &ldquo;been arrested and enquiries are ongoing,&rdquo; the police said.</p>



<p><strong>Read More</strong>:<em><a href="https://time.com/7372763/epstein-files-united-kingdom-peter-mandelson-prince-andrew-starmer/" > How the Epstein Files Broke Britain</a></em></p>



<p>Starmer&rsquo;s chief of staff, Morgan McSweeney, resigned on Sunday, in the wake of the controversy. In a statement, he took responsibility for advising Starmer to appoint Mandelson in the ambassador role.</p>



<p>&ldquo;The decision to appoint Peter Mandelson was wrong. He has damaged our party, our country and trust in politics itself,&rdquo; said McSweeney. &ldquo;When asked, I advised the Prime Minister to make that appointment and I take full responsibility for that advice.&rdquo;</p>



<p>On Monday morning, Starmer&#8217;s executive director of communications, Tim Allan, also stepped down.</p>



<p>However, the departures have done little to curb calls for Starmer to resign.</p>



<p>Kemi Badenoch, leader of the opposition Conservative Party, argued that Starmer &ldquo;has to take responsibility for his own terrible decisions&rdquo; and said his position is &ldquo;<a href="https://x.com/KemiBadenoch/status/2020601071433818613"  target="_blank">untenable</a>.&rdquo; Meanwhile, Anas Sarwar, head of the Scottish Labour Party, said the &ldquo;leadership in Downing Street has to change.&rdquo;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
