<p>Denmark&rsquo;s foreign minister, Lars L&oslash;kke Rasmussen, told reporters during a visit to Washington this week that Denmark was reinforcing security in the Arctic &ldquo;by committing additional funds for military capabilities&mdash;not dogsleds, but ships, drones, fighter jets, etc,&rdquo; referring to an often-repeated jibe by Trump that Denmark&rsquo;s military presence on the island consisted entirely of dogsleds. </p>



<p><strong>Read More:</strong> <a href="https://time.com/7346173/trump-tariffs-india-china-the-united-states/" ><em>Trump, Tariffs, and the Rewiring of the American Empire</em></a></p>



